1. Prepare Environment

Create at least 2 VMs in Proxmox:
1 Master node (control plane) → manages the cluster.
1+ Worker nodes (slaves) → run workloads (pods).
⚙️ Example VM spec:
OS: Ubuntu 22.04 LTS (recommended)
Master: 2 CPU, 4GB RAM, 20GB disk
Worker: 2 CPU, 2GB RAM, 20GB disk
Network: All VMs in the same LAN (so they can communicate).

2. Install Dependencies (on all nodes)
# Update system
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
# Install required packages
sudo apt install -y apt-transport-https ca-certificates curl
# Disable swap (Kubernetes requires it)
sudo swapoff -a
sudo sed -i '/ swap / s/^/#/' /etc/fstab

3. Install Docker or container runtime
sudo apt install -y containerd
sudo mkdir -p /etc/containerd
containerd config default | sudo tee /etc/containerd/config.toml
sudo systemctl restart containerd
sudo systemctl enable containerd

4. Install kubeadm, kubelet, kubectl (on all nodes)
# Update and install dependencies
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install -y apt-transport-https ca-certificates curl gpg
# Add Kubernetes signing key
sudo curl -fsSL https://pkgs.k8s.io/core:/stable:/v1.30/deb/Release.key | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/kubernetes-apt-keyring.gpg
# Add Kubernetes APT repository
echo "deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/kubernetes-apt-keyring.gpg] https://pkgs.k8s.io/core:/stable:/v1.30/deb/ /" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/kubernetes.list
# Update package index again
sudo apt-get update
# Install kubelet, kubeadm and kubectl
sudo apt-get install -y kubelet kubeadm kubectl
# Prevent automatic updates (recommended for cluster stability)
sudo apt-mark hold kubelet kubeadm kubectl
curl -s https://packages.cloud.google.com/apt/doc/apt-key.gpg | sudo apt-key add -
echo "deb https://apt.kubernetes.io/ kubernetes-xenial main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/kubernetes.list
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y kubelet kubeadm kubectl
sudo apt-mark hold kubelet kubeadm kubectl

5. Initialize Master Node
# Enable immediately
sudo sysctl -w net.ipv4.ip_forward=1
# Make it permanent across reboots
echo "net.ipv4.ip_forward = 1" | sudo tee -a /etc/sysctl.conf
# Reload sysctl config
sudo sysctl -p

Verify
cat /proc/sys/net/ipv4/ip_forward
For master node
sudo kubeadm init --pod-network-cidr=10.244.0.0/16

6. Setup kubectl for master
mkdir -p $HOME/.kube
sudo cp -i /etc/kubernetes/admin.conf $HOME/.kube/config
sudo chown $(id -u):$(id -g) $HOME/.kube/config




